<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-96-0676 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors construct a flow model to determine the effect of temperatureand a magnetic field on the magnetohydrodynamic and thermodynamic convectionmechanisms of a magnetic liquid layer with internal heat sources. Boundaryconditions for the Rayleigh and Hartmann numbers are established andother thermal considerations, including thermal conductivity and thermalexpansion as well as the contribution of temperature gradients to thestratification behavior of the liquid, are incorporated.</TEXT></DOC>